Ampify ðŸŽ¸

AI-powered guitar amp setting recommender

Overview

Ampify is an AI application that takes in a song input (audio snippet, chords, or metadata) and outputs recommended guitar amp settings (amp model, gain, EQ, reverb, presence, effects). Itâ€™s designed to help guitarists quickly dial in tones that match the feel of a song without endless tweaking.

The system uses a FastAPI backend with audio analysis (via librosa) and optional ML models (PyTorch). A React + Tailwind frontend provides an upload form, visual knob controls, and preset management.

This project is structured for rapid prototyping â€” start with the rule-based MVP, then layer in machine learning models and cloud deployment.

Features

Input options:  provide song title/artist

Output: JSON with amp model + normalized knob values (gain, bass, mid, treble, presence, reverb)
 
 AI core: rule-based predictor (MVP) + hooks for PyTorch models

 Feedback loop: collect user ratings to refine future predictions

Deploy-ready: Dockerized backend, frontend deployable on Vercel/Netlify, backend on Render/Cloud Run

Extensible: support for exporting presets to popular amp sims (planned)

Tech Stack

Frontend: React + TypeScript + TailwindCSS

Backend: FastAPI (Python), librosa, optional PyTorch

Storage: S3 (or any object store), Postgres (Supabase recommended)

Infra: Docker, GitHub Actions (CI/CD), Vercel/Render/Cloud Run

Optional: Redis for job queueing, Hugging Face/Replicate for GPU inference

Video link: https://youtu.be/GyBEt7Db5io

Setup insructions:
1. download repository
2. Go to backend of project (cd tone-ai-backend)
3. install requirements (pip install -r requirements.txt)
4. Start Backend (uvicorn app:app --reload)
5. Go to frontend of project( cd front_end)
6. Install npm (npm install)
7. Run front end (npm run dev)
8. Input any song and click "make amp"

Authors: Carter Foster, Daniel Robinson

